div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00"><b class="ssrcss-hmf8ql-BoldText e5tfeyi3">Africa has a rich and complex history but there is widespread ignorance of this heritage. A celebrated British historian once said there was only the history of Europeans in Africa. Zeinab Badawi has been asking what is behind this lack of knowledge and looking at the historical record for an African history series on BBC World News.</b></p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The Great Pyramid of Giza in Cairo is rightly considered one of the seven wonders of the ancient world. But travel further south along the River Nile and you will find a thousand pyramids that belonged to the Kingdom of Kush, in what is now Sudan. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Kush was an African superpower and its influence extended to what is now called the Middle East. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The kingdom lasted for many hundreds of years and in the eighth Century BC, it conquered Egypt and governed for the best part of a century.  </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">What remains of the kingdom is equally impressive. More than 300 of these pyramids are still intact,  almost untouched since they were built nearly 3,000 years ago. </p></div></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1onuslq-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="line" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/464/cpsprodpb/18385/production/_96750299_line976.jpg" width="464" height="2" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span></div></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00"><b class="ssrcss-hmf8ql-BoldText e5tfeyi3">Zeinab Badawi</b></p></div></div><div id="piano-inline1"></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1mimstg-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="Zeinab Badawi in a museum" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/11AD5/production/_96750427_statuesofthekingsofkushsudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg" width="976" height="300" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span><span class="ssrcss-1ecljvk-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image copyright</span>Kush Communications</span></div></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00"><i class="ssrcss-xbdn93-ItalicText e5tfeyi2">&quot;There has been a way of seeing Africa in terms of poverty and conflict which has become a kind of shorthand for the continent that still persists today.&quot;</i></p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">You can watch History of Africa on BBC World News at the following times: </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Saturday 02:10 GMT; 15:10 GMT</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Sunday 09:10 GMT; 21:10 GMT</p></div></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1onuslq-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="line" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/464/cpsprodpb/9D71/production/_96750304_line976.jpg" width="464" height="2" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span></div></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Some of the best examples can be found in Jebel Barkal in northern Sudan, declared a <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629/http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1073" class="ssrcss-9nsdc6-InlineLink e1no5rhv0">world heritage site</a> by the UN&#x27;s cultural agency, Unesco.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Here you can find pyramids, tombs, temples and burial chambers complete with painted scenes and writings that Unesco describes as masterpieces &quot;of creative genius demonstrating the artistic, social, political and religious values of a human group for more than 2,000 years&quot;.</p></div></div><div id="piano-inline2"></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-4lxdld-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="A general view shows 27 January 2006 the Meroe archaeological site, 300 kms north of the Sudanese capital Khartoum" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/18AB/production/_96751360_gettyimages-160635474.jpg" width="976" height="650" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span><span class="ssrcss-1ecljvk-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image copyright</span>AFP</span></div></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Some years ago I visited these pyramids. On my return to the UK, I asked my parents what they knew of their country&#x27;s historic sites. Not much, it turned out. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This was odd since both of them could tell you a lot about Henry VIII and key points in British history.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">I wondered given that my parents did not know enough about their own country&#x27;s history whether this was likely to be true of many other Africans.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">And as I talked to people I discovered that this was indeed the case. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">A few years later, at Unesco&#x27;s Paris headquarters, I saw on the bookshelves of Ethiopian-born Deputy Director-General Getachew Engida a collection of volumes - the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629/http://www.unesco.org/new/en/social-and-human-sciences/themes/general-history-of-africa/" class="ssrcss-9nsdc6-InlineLink e1no5rhv0">General History of Africa</a>. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This, it turned out, is one of Unesco&#x27;s and the continent&#x27;s best kept secrets: Africa&#x27;s history written by African scholars.</p></div></div><div id="piano-inline3"></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1xtcmof-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="A bas-relief in one of the pyramids at the Meroe archaeological site, about five km (three miles) east of the Nile." srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/149F0/production/_96746448_relief-characters-resized.jpg" width="976" height="549" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span><span class="ssrcss-1ecljvk-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image copyright</span>Getty Images</span></div><figcaption class="ssrcss-1rnnz6t-StyledFigureCaption e34k3c22"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image caption</span>The carvings at the pyramids in Sudan give an insight into the life in the Kingdom of Kush</figcaption></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The project was conceived in the early 1960s during the period of rapid decolonisation in Africa. Some of the newly independent African leaders decided that after decolonising their countries they also wanted to decolonise their history.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Western historians had lamented the lack of written records in some African countries and had used this as a reason to legitimise such neglect.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Unesco helped African scholars put together the project, recruiting 350 experts, mostly from across Africa and from a range of disciplines, to compile eight volumes, starting from prehistory and continuing to the modern era. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The eighth volume was completed in 1990 and a ninth is now being worked on. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Unesco took the controversial step of starting the volumes with the origins of humankind, setting out the theory of evolution. By doing so, they risked incurring the wrath of Christian and Muslim communities in some African countries where there was, and still is, a widespread belief in creationism.</p></div></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1xtcmof-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="Paintings inside the pyramids" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/D8A8/production/_96746455_insidethekushitepyramidssudan.imagecredit-kushcommunications.jpg" width="976" height="549" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span><span class="ssrcss-1ecljvk-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image copyright</span>Kush Communications</span></div><figcaption class="ssrcss-1rnnz6t-StyledFigureCaption e34k3c22"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image caption</span>There are also paintings inside the pyramids in Sudan</figcaption></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Kenyan palaeontologist Richard Leakey, who contributed to volume one, says he still believes that the fact humans originated in Africa is anathema to some Westerners, who would prefer to deny their African origins. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The story of the Kingdom of Kush, a superpower in western Asia as well as Africa, where queens could rule in their own right, is also often overlooked.  </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This is also true of the Kingdom of Aksum, described as one of the four greatest civilisations of the ancient world.  </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The Aksumite kings controlled trade in the Red Sea from their base in what is modern day Eritrea and Ethiopia.  They were also the first rulers in Africa to embrace Christianity and make it the kingdom&#x27;s official religion. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This history is little known, both in Africa and elsewhere, because a lot of academics and teachers in African countries have been a product of colonial education themselves, and so they could not receive a comprehensive and chronological account of their own history.</p></div></div><div data-component="image-block" class="ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810"><figure class="ssrcss-md0xev-StyledFigure e34k3c23"><div class="ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21"><span class="ssrcss-1xtcmof-Placeholder e16icw910"><span><noscript><img alt="Aksum obelisk field" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 240w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 320w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 480w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 624w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 800w, https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg 976w" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20210729162629im_/https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/827D/production/_96750433_gettyimages-3018911.jpg" width="976" height="549" loading="lazy" class="ssrcss-1drmwog-Image ee0ct7c0"/></noscript></span></span><span class="ssrcss-1ecljvk-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image copyright</span>AFP</span></div><figcaption class="ssrcss-1rnnz6t-StyledFigureCaption e34k3c22"><span class="ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0">image caption</span>Ancient stellae from the old kingdom can be seen in the present day Ethiopian town of Axum</figcaption></figure></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">My own Sudanese parents were fluent in English, and highly educated, but by and large were taught according to a Western curriculum.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Even when they looked at their own history, it would have been through the perspective of Western scholars. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">One such view was reflected in the comments by Hugh Trevor-Roper, widely regarded as one of Britain&#x27;s foremost historians. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">He said in 1965: &quot;Perhaps, in the future, there will be some African history to teach. But at present there is none, or very little: there is only the history of the Europeans in Africa. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">&quot;The rest is largely darkness, like the history of pre-European, pre-Columbian America. And darkness is not a subject for history.&quot;</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The fact that very few people know about the volumes compiled under the auspices of Unesco also tells you something. You wonder why leaders did not want to shine more light on it. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">I am not suggesting there was a conspiracy, of course. Just that there was not enough emphasis placed on African history by either African or non-African leaders.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This is of particular interest for Africa, though, because it has been infantilised to a degree that we have not seen in any other region of the world. </p></div></div><div data-component="crosshead-block" class="ssrcss-mysbf6-ComponentWrapper-CrossheadComponentWrapper e1xue1i84"><h2 class="ssrcss-ve3352-StyledHeading e1fj1fc10">Challenging the stereotype</h2></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">This is partly because there has been a way of seeing Africa in terms of poverty and conflict - the coup, the war, the famine, the corruption - which has become a kind of shorthand for the continent that still persists today.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Development issues in Africa still, to a large extent, emphasise charitable aspects and aid. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Although this is done with the best will in the world it has nevertheless fed into this representation of Africa, whereby it is assumed that, in order for its people to develop and for them to have enough to eat, they have to rely on outsiders.</p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">As someone who was born in Africa, and who came to the UK as an infant, I have the benefit of understanding both cultures. </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">The General History of Africa is a start and Unesco plans to incorporate its research into school syllabuses across the continent.  </p></div></div><div data-component="text-block" class="ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i85"><div class="ssrcss-18snukc-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1"><p class="ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00">Hopefully, future generations will have a better idea of their history and see there is much for them to be proud of from their past . A past which provides the foundation for an even greater future. </p></div></div><section data-component="tag-list" class="ssrcss-ukwdbg-SectionWrapper e1nh2i2l2"><div class="ssrcss-1vipmlp-StyledTagContainer ed0g1kj1"><div class="ssrcss-4c4zzp-SectionHeaderWrapper e1nh2i2l3"><div class="ssrcss-1y8kwfd-SectionHeader eik4du50"><h2 class="ssrcss-a1ws5s-StyledHeading e1fj1fc10">Related Topics</h2></div></div><div class="ssrcss-i7uuy0-Cluster e1ihwmse1"><ul role="list" spacing="2" class="ssrcss-d7aixc-ClusterItems e1ihwmse0"><li><a href="/web/20210729162629/https://www.bbc.com/news/topics/c8nq32jw58pt" class="ssrcss-1yno9a1-StyledLink ed0g1kj0">History</a></li></ul></div></div></section><section data-component="see-alsos" class="ssrcss-ukwdbg-SectionWrapper e1nh2i2l2"><div class="ssrcss-4c4zzp-SectionHeaderWrapper e1nh2i2l3"><div class="ssrcss-1y8kwfd-SectionHeader eik4du50"><h2 class="ssrcss-a1ws5s-StyledHeading e1fj1fc10">More on this story</h2></div></div><ul role="list" spacing="responsive" class="ssrcss-1rw2j9a-Stack e1y4nx260"><li class="ssrcss-1as76fj-PromoItem e1nh2i2l4"><div class="ssrcss-12gv2og-Promo ett16tt0"><div class="ssrcss-1wok6t6-PromoNoImage e98n9a20"><div class="ssrcss-som5se-PromoContent e1f5wbog7"><div spacing="2" class="ssrcss-rjdkox-Stack e1y4nx260"><a href="/web/20210729162629/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-39972853" class="ssrcss-19scfkb-PromoLink e1f5wbog0"><span role="text"><p class="ssrcss-nff25b-PromoHeadline e1f5wbog4"><span aria-hidden="false">The Qatari princess, Angelina Jolie and the battle of the pyramids</span></p></span></a></div><div spacing="4" class="ssrcss-18k1qz4-Stack e1y4nx260"><div><dl class="ssrcss-1bfmg49-MetadataStrip e1ojgjhb